# Page Template: Settings Page

> Reference template for building settings/configuration pages in {{ display_name }}.

## Purpose

Settings pages allow users to configure application preferences, account settings, and integrations. Settings are grouped into logical sections with a sidebar or tab navigation.

## Layout Structure

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Header / Navigation Bar                          │
├──────────┬───────────────────────────────────────┤
│          │  Settings                               │
│          ├────────────┬──────────────────────────┤
│  Sidebar │  Settings  │  Section Title            │
│          │  Nav       │                            │
│  (nav)   │            │  Setting Group 1           │
│          │  > General │  ┌──────────────────────┐ │
│          │    Profile │  │ Label    [input     ] │ │
│          │    Notif.  │  │ Label    [toggle    ] │ │
│          │    Team    │  │ Label    [select   v] │ │
│          │    Billing │  └──────────────────────┘ │
│          │    API     │                            │
│          │            │  Setting Group 2           │
│          │            │  ┌──────────────────────┐ │
│          │            │  │ ...                   │ │
│          │            │  └──────────────────────┘ │
│          │            │                            │
│          │            │         [Save Changes]     │
└──────────┴────────────┴──────────────────────────┘
```

## Settings Sections

### General

- Application name / branding
- Language and locale
- Timezone
- Date/number format

### Profile

- Display name and avatar
- Email address
- Password change
- Two-factor authentication (if {{ use_auth }})

### Notifications

- Email notification preferences
- In-app notification preferences
- Digest frequency (real-time / daily / weekly)

### Team (if applicable)

- Team member list with roles
- Invite new members
- Remove members
- Role management

### Billing (if applicable)

- Current plan display
- Usage metrics
- Payment method
- Invoice history

### API / Integrations

- API key management (create, revoke)
- Webhook configuration
- Third-party integrations

## Components

### Settings Navigation

- Vertical sidebar list of sections
- Active section highlighted
- Sections can be nested (General > Appearance)

### Setting Group

- Group title with optional description
- Form fields: text inputs, toggles, selects, radio groups
- Each field: label, input, help text (optional), validation error (optional)

### Save Behavior

- **Option A:** Save button per section (explicit save)
- **Option B:** Auto-save with debounce (immediate feedback)
- Show success/error toast after save

## States

| State | Behavior |
|-------|----------|
| Loading | Skeleton for form fields |
| Pristine | Save button disabled |
| Dirty | Save button enabled, unsaved indicator |
| Saving | Save button shows spinner |
| Saved | Success toast, button resets |
| Error | Inline validation + error toast |

## Design Notes ({{ design_style }})

{% if design_style == "minimal-clean" %}
- Left sidebar navigation, clean form layout
- Subtle section dividers
- Muted save button until changes are made
{% elif design_style == "corporate-professional" %}
- Card-based sections with headers
- Clear form labels with help text
- Standard button styles for actions
{% elif design_style == "playful-modern" %}
- Colorful section icons in navigation
- Rounded input fields
- Animated toggle switches
{% endif %}

## Data Requirements

- Load: `GET /api/settings`
- Save: `PATCH /api/settings/<section>`
- Team: `GET /api/team/members`, `POST /api/team/invite`

## Accessibility

- Settings nav uses proper `nav` landmark
- Form fields have associated labels
- Toggle switches have accessible names
- Keyboard navigation through all settings
- Save confirmation announced to screen readers
